'''Crysencio Jilbert Sylverio Cirro Summerville''' (born 30 October 2001) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|WestHamU}} football club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Feyenoord ===
Born in [[Rotterdam]] to [[Afro-Surinamese]] parents, Summerville played youth football at RVVV Noorderkwartier before joining the [[Feyenoord]] academy in 2008.<ref name="WF">{{Worldfootball.net|crysencio-summerville|new_id=pe499863}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Beck |first=Tim |date=4 December 2018 |title=Wie is Feyenoord-dilemma Crysencio Summerville? |url=http://www.elfvoetbal.nl/Binnenland/274653/Wie-is-Feyenoord-dilemma-Crysencio-Summerville- |access-date=25 September 2020 |website=Elfvoetbal.nl |language=nl}}</ref> In March 2018, he signed his first professional contract with Feyenoord; a contract lasting until the summer of 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 March 2018 |title=Eerste profcontract voor Crysencio Summerville |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/eerste-profcontract-voor-crysencio-summerville |access-date=25 September 2020 |website=feyenoord.nl |publisher=Feyenoord |language=nl}}</ref>

On 12 December 2018, he joined [[FC Dordrecht]] on loan until the end of the 2018–19 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 December 2018 |title=Toptalent van Feyenoord naar FC Dordrecht |trans-title=Top talent from Feyenoord to FC Dordrecht |url=https://www.fcdordrecht.nl/2018/12/12/toptalent-van-feyenoord-naar-dordt/ |publisher=[[FC Dordrecht]] |language=Dutch}}</ref> He made his [[Eerste Divisie]] debut for Dordrecht on 13 January 2019 in a game against [[FC Den Bosch|Den Bosch]], as a 70th-minute substitute for [[Oussama Zamouri]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 January 2019 |title=Game Report by Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/01/13/netherlands/eerste-divisie/bvo-fc-dordrecht/fc-den-bosch/2794563/ |publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> On 29 January 2019, he made his starting eleven debut for the club, scoring his first goal as a professional footballer in the sixth minute.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 December 2018 |title=FC Dordrecht laat zege uit handen glippen |trans-title=FC Dordrechts lets win slip |url=https://www.fcdordrecht.nl/2019/01/29/fc-dordrecht-laat-zege-uit-handen-glippen/ |publisher=[[FC Dordrecht]] |language=Dutch}}</ref>

[[File:Crysencio Summerville July 2019.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Summerville in 2019 with [[Feyenoord]]]]

In August 2019, he joined fellow [[Eredivisie]] side [[ADO Den Haag]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 August 2019 |title=Crysencio Summerville op huurbasis naar ADO Den Haag |url=https://adodenhaag.nl/nl/nieuws/laatste-nieuws/1e-elftal/8025-crysencio-summerville-op-huurbasis-naar-ado-den-haag |access-date=26 September 2020 |publisher=ADO Den Haag |language=nl}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 31 August 2019 in a 1–0 win against [[VVV Venlo]] in a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 September 2020 |title=ADO Den Haag 1 VVV Venlo 0 |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/eredivisie/2019-2020/live-ado-den-haag-vvv-venlo_mtc1154368/live.shtml |publisher=Eurosport}}</ref> On 26 October 2019, he scored his first Eredivisie goal for ADO Den Haag on 26 October 2019 in a 2–0 win against [[Vitesse Arnhem]], becoming the youngest goalscorer for the club in the Eredivisie.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 October 2019 |title=Summerville jongste ADO-doelpuntenmaker ooit: 'Drie punten zijn belangrijker' |trans-title=Summerville youngest ADO goal scorer ever: "Three points are more important" |url=https://www.omroepwest.nl/media/30370/Summerville-jongste-ADO-doelpuntenmaker-ooit-Drie-punten-zijn-belangrijker |publisher=[[Omroep West]] |language=Dutch}}</ref> He impressed for the club during his spell, scoring two goals and gained three assists for the side.<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 May 2020 |title=ADO Den Haag neemt weer afscheid van lichtpuntje Summerville |trans-title=ADO Den Haag says goodbye to the bright spot of Summerville |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/ado-den-haag-neemt-weer-afscheid-van-lichtpuntje-summerville |access-date=26 September 2020 |website=Voetbal International}}</ref>

He returned to Feyenoord at the end of his loan spell ahead of the [[2020–21 Eredivisie]] season, with [[Voetbal International]] reporting on 17 August 2020 that Summerville had turned down a new extended contract offer at Feyenoord.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Krabbendam |first=Martijn |date=17 August 2020 |title=Summerville mist perspectief bij Feyenoord en tekent niet bij |trans-title=Summerville lacks perspective at Feyenoord and does not sign up |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/summerville-mist-perspectief-bij-feyenoord-en-tekent-niet-bij |access-date=26 September 2020 |website=Voetbal International}}</ref>

=== Leeds United ===
On 16 September 2020, Summerville joined [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] for an undisclosed fee, signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sobot |first=Lee |date=16 September 2020 |title=Leeds United sign winger Crysencio Summerville from Feyenoord |language=en |work=Yorkshire Evening Post |url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leeds-united-sign-winger-crysencio-summerville-feyenoord-2973838 |access-date=26 September 2020}}</ref>

He made his debut on 17 September 2021 against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], in the Premier League, coming on for [[Raphinha]] in the 67th minute.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58510618|last=Magowan|first=Alistair|title=Newcastle 1–1 Leeds – Saint-Maximin equaliser earns point|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=17 September 2021}}</ref>

In August 2022 Summerville agreed a new contract at Leeds until 2026.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/cqvg3949q32o Leeds contract extension]</ref>

On 23 October 2022, Summerville scored his first [[Premier League]] goal in a 3–2 defeat against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] at [[Elland Road]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63274134|title=Leeds 2–3 Fulham|last=Dawkes|first=Phil|work=BBC Sport|date=23 October 2022}}</ref> On 29 October, he scored the winning goal in the 89th minute in a 2–1 victory over [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], making it his club's first win at [[Anfield]] since April 2001, simultaneously ending Liverpool's 29-game unbeaten streak at home in the Premier League.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63354918|last=Rose|first=Gary|title=Liverpool 1–2 Leeds|work=BBC Sport|date=29 October 2022}}</ref> On 5 November 2022, he scored another late winning goal to give Leeds a come-from-behind 4–3 win at home against Bournemouth.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Leeds 4–3 Bournemouth|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|last=Johnston|first=Neil|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63436261|date=5 November 2022|access-date=2022-11-05}}</ref> His goal in Leeds’ 4–3 away loss  at [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 12 November brought Summerville's league tally to four goals in four consecutive games, as the Premier League went on hiatus for the World Cup.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/fooball/63523918|title=Tottenham 4–3 Leeds|language=en-GB|last=Howarth|first=Matthew|work=BBC Sport|date=12 November 2022|access-date=5 November 2022}}{{Dead link|date=September 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref> However, he did not find the net again in either the league or the cup for the remainder of the season and found himself often substituted or, when not in the starting XI, coming on usually as a direct second-half replacement for [[Brenden Aaronson]]; Leeds United suffered from poor form during this period and were consequently relegated from the Premier League.

[[File:Crysencio Summerville (cropped).jpeg|thumb|Summerville with [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] in 2023|283x283px]]

Summerville scored a brace in an eight-minute spell at [[Carrow Road]] in a late-in-the-game 3–2 win on 21 October 2023. This was the first time since May 2021 that Leeds had had three victories in a row and moved them up to third in the [[EFL Championship|Championship]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67108820|title=Norwich 2–3 Leeds|work=BBC Sport|date=21 October 2023|access-date=29 October 2023}}</ref> He followed this up seven days later with another pair of goals, both scored in the first half, in the team's 4–1 home victory over [[Huddersfield Town F.C.|Huddersfield]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67178996|title=Leeds 4–1 Huddersfield: Derby Delight for Leeds Against Tame Huddersfield|work=BBC Sport|date=28 October 2023|access-date=29 October 2023}}</ref> Summerville further proved instrumental in the Leeds side, where, after an assist to [[Joël Piroe|Piroe]] in a 2–1 win against [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth]] on 11 November 2023,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67318259|title=Leeds United 2–1 Plymouth Argyle: Dan James and Joel Piroe on target for Whites|work=BBC Sport|date=11 November 2023}}</ref> he would have a goal contribution in five consecutive games. In 2024, Leeds went on a 16-game unbeaten run, in which Summerville played every game, ending in a 2–1 loss to [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry]] in April.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68696768|title=Coventry City 2–1 Leeds United: Sky Blues stay in play-off hunt as Leeds miss chance to go top|work=BBC Sport|date=6 April 2024}}</ref> Afterwards, Leeds went on a string of bad form, achieving only one win in six games, a win at [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]], where Summerville netted a brace and an assist in a dramatic 3–4 scoreline.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c51np022e09t|title=Middlesbrough 3–4 Leeds United: Daniel Farke's side move second in Championship with win|work=BBC Sport|date=22 April 2024}}</ref> Leeds finished third in the campaign, with Summerville named the Championship Player of the Season and a place in the Championship Team of the Season at the 2024 [[EFL Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.efl.com/news/2024/april/14/crysencio-summerville-named-the-sky-bet-championship-player-of-the-season/|title=Crysencio Summerville named the Sky Bet Championship Player of the Season |publisher=EFL|date=14 April 2024}}</ref> In the second leg of the Championship play-off semi-final, he scored the fourth goal in a 4–0 hammering at [[Elland Road]] to [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich]] on 16 May.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cw4rzmywx4yt|title=Leeds hammer Norwich to cruise into play-off final |work=BBC Sport|date=16 May 2024}}</ref> Following their win, Leeds progressed to the play-off final, where they lost 0–1 to [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] at [[Wembley Stadium|Wembley]] on 25 May,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cd11vdnwwjdt|title=Adam Armstrong goal sends Saints back up to Premier League |work=BBC Sport|date=26 May 2024}}</ref> putting an end to hopes of a rebound return to the [[Premier League]]. He ended the season with 21 goals and 10 assists in 49 appearances, achieving the status of top scorer for the Whites.<ref name="6things">{{cite web | title=Six things you need to know about Crysencio Summerville | publisher=West Ham United F.C. | date=4 August 2024 | url=https://www.whufc.com/news/six-things-you-need-know-about-crysencio-summerville | access-date=4 August 2024}}</ref>

=== West Ham United ===
On 3 August 2024, Summerville joined [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] for a fee in excess of £25&nbsp;million. He signed a five-year contract with an option for a sixth year.<ref>{{cite web | title=Crysencio Summerville: West Ham complete deal for Leeds forward | website=BBC Sport | date=3 August 2024 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/czd99xv5lq0o | access-date=4 August 2024}}</ref>
He made his West Ham  debut on 17 August, coming on as a 73rd minute substitute for [[Jarrod Bowen]] in a 2–1 home defeat by [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Hammers beaten by Aston Villa in season opener | publisher=West Ham United F.C. | date=22 August 2024| url=https://www.whufc.com/news/match-report-hammers-beaten-aston-villa-season-opener | access-date=23 August 2024}}</ref> His first goal for West Ham came on 27 October, the first goal in a 2–1 win against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Summerville and Bowen strike in second half to beat Manchester United | publisher=West Ham United F.C. | date=27 October 2024 | url=https://www.whufc.com/news/match-report-summerville-and-bowen-strike-second-half-beat-manchester-united | access-date=27 October 2024}}</ref>

Summerville suffered a hamstring injury that required surgery in an FA Cup tie against Aston Villa on 10 January 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/west-ham-injury-boost-summerville-potter-earthy-b1242985.html|title=West Ham injury boost as Graham Potter provides positive Crysencio Summerville update|last=Tabuteau|first=Sam|website=The Standard|date=14 August 2025|access-date=31 August 2025}}</ref> He made his return to the first team as a substitute in a 3–0 league defeat of [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] at the [[City Ground]] on 31 August 2025, being directly involved in the Hammers' first two goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/clydd7xpggnt|title= Premier League: Brighton beat Man City and West Ham thrash Forest|website=BBC Sport|date=31 August 2025|access-date=31 August 2025}}</ref>

== International career ==
Born in the Netherlands, Summerville is of Surinamese descent.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Crysencio Summerville |url=https://www.sport.de/fussball/pe499863/crysencio-summerville/ |website=sport.de}}</ref> He won the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] with the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team]], scoring a goal in the group game against Germany and appearing as a substitute in the final against Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 May 2018 |title=Italy U17 v Netherlands U17 game report |url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2024319--italy-vs-netherlands/ |publisher=[[UEFA]]}}</ref> On 27 May 2026, [[Ronald Koeman]] revealed that Summerville was part of the [[Netherlands national football team|26 men squad]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Netherlands' 26-Man Squad For 2026 World Cup Named by Ronald Koeman|url=https://www.givemesport.com/netherlands-2026-world-cup-squad/
|website=givemesport.com}}</ref>

